other_tests.findings: The liver is mildly echogenic, which may reflect fatty deposition. There is no intra- or extra-hepatic biliary ductal dilatation. The gallbladder is tensely distended without mural edema or pericholecystic fluid. Two gallstones are seen measuring up to 1.7 cm. One may be impacted in the gallbladder neck. Sonographic Murphy's sign was unreliable in the setting of pain medication.
